<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <title>Git Fight!</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="/style.css">
    <script type="text/javascript" src="http://ajax.googleapis.com/ajax/libs/jquery/1.4.2/jquery.min.js"></script>
    <script type="text/javascript" src="/app.js"></script>
  </head>
  <body>
    <h1>Git Fight!</h1>

    <p class="info">Enter two GitHub usernames into the boxes below, and my algorithm will work out who is the better contributor by analyzing their GitHub stats.</p>

    <form id="fight" action="/fight" method="get">
      <input type="text" name="user_1" id="user_1" value="<%= h @user_1 ? @user_1.username : '' %>"> <span class="vs">vs.</span>
      <input type="text" name="user_2" value="<%= h @user_2 ? @user_2.username : '' %>">
      <input type="submit" value="Fight!">
    </form>
    
    <div id="replaceable">
      <%= yield %>
    </div>
    
    <p class="info disclaimer">Git Fight! is not associated with GitHub. These figures are based in fact, but they are only a weak proxy for a user's actual contribution levels. User data is cached for a week at a time. Copyright &copy; 2010 <a href=
"http://blog.bloople.net/">Brenton Fletcher</a>. <a href="http://github.com/bloopletech/sinatra_apps/tree/master/git_fight/">Source on GitHub</a>.</p>
  </body>
</html>
